column3: What I am interested in working on::"Problem I'm currently working on solving: Young borrowers under 30 face systematic barriers within European credit scoring systems that stem from the fundamental design of traditional risk assessment methodologies. column1: With major players such as Schufa Holding AG
column2: Experian
column3: and other commercial listed companies controlling significant portions of European credit information systems
column4: young borrowers who have primarily engaged with alternative financial services or maintained minimal traditional banking relationships may find their creditworthiness inadequately represented in standard assessment processes.

column1: Solution: Behavioral credit scoring represents a paradigm shift in financial risk assessment
column2: leveraging non-traditional data sources to evaluate creditworthiness. This approach analyzes patterns in digital transactions
column5: and other behavioral indicators to complement or replace traditional metrics like payment history and debt-to-income ratios. In Europe
column6: where 22% of adults lack access to traditional credit products
column7: behavioral scoring offers potential solutions for financial inclusion while introducing complex regulatory considerations under evolving EU frameworks."
